### Music Loop Not Playing Fix (2026-04-08)

User report: "the music loop is not playing on the landing page for a property"

**Root Cause Analysis:**
The AmbientAudioPlayer had several issues with its useEffect hooks:
1. The cleanup function was pausing audio whenever the `activeTrack` object reference changed (even if URL was the same)
2. Browser autoplay restrictions caused initial play to fail silently
3. No proper handling of the `canplaythrough` event before attempting playback
4. The `isPlaying` state could become stale in the effect closure

**Fix Applied to `frontend/src/components/media/AmbientAudioPlayer.tsx`:**
1. Added `currentUrlRef` to track actual URL changes (not object reference changes)
2. Separated audio source setup into its own effect
3. Added `canplaythrough` event listener to attempt playback only when audio is ready
4. Added play/pause event listeners to sync `isPlaying` state with actual audio element state
5. Added `hasUserInteracted` state to track when user clicks play, allowing autoplay on subsequent track changes
6. Moved cleanup (pause + clear src) to a separate unmount-only effect with eslint-disable comment
7. Initial volume is now set before attempting playback

