## Session: 2026-04-11 - QGIS 3D Map Dedicated Admin Section

### Request
Refactor the QGIS 3D scene feature from a generic media upload into a dedicated "3D Map" tab in the property editor with:
- Separate admin section (not mixed with media uploads)
- Security sanitization for uploaded ZIP files
- Description field for the map
- Instructions on preparing maps with QGIS

### Implementation

#### Backend Security (pkg/ziputil/ziputil.go)
Added comprehensive ZIP security validation:
- `SceneLimits` struct: MaxZipSize (50MB), MaxExtractedSize (100MB), MaxFileCount (500), MaxFileSize (20MB), MaxPathDepth (10)
- `AllowedExtensions` whitelist: html, js, json, css, images, fonts, 3D models (gltf, glb, obj, mtl, bin)
- `DangerousPatterns` regex list: document.cookie, localStorage, sessionStorage, parent.document, external scripts, eval(), innerHTML assignment
- `SafePatterns` allowlist: THREE., Q3D., Qgis2threejs (to reduce false positives)
- `AnalyzeZIP()` - Pre-scan ZIP for size, file count, symlinks, disallowed extensions
- `ExtractSafe()` - Extract with whitelist enforcement and size limits
- `ValidateSceneContent()` - Post-extraction HTML/JS pattern scan
- Refactored `Extract()` to use `ExtractSafe()` internally

#### Backend Service (internal/service/media_svc.go)
- Added `Description` field to `UploadSceneInput`
- Modified `UploadScene()` to:
  - Call `AnalyzeZIP()` before extraction with validation
  - Call `ValidateSceneContent()` post-extraction (reject if >5 warnings)
  - Store file_count and original_filename in metadata
  - Store description in Caption field

#### Backend Handler (internal/handler/media_handler.go)
- Added description field parsing from POST form data

#### Frontend API (frontend/src/api/index.ts)
- Updated `uploadScene()` to accept optional description parameter

#### Frontend Component (frontend/src/components/property/Map3DTab.tsx)
New dedicated component with:
- Introduction card explaining 3D property maps
- Collapsible accordion with step-by-step QGIS instructions
- Upload section with drag-and-drop, description textarea, security notice
- When scene exists: embedded QGISSceneViewer preview, scene info, editable description
- Actions: Save Description, Replace Map, Delete Map

#### Frontend PropertyEdit.tsx
